<subSubSection id="07E113A1FFCE4853FF4ED646FF482E5B" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="4F44402AFFCE4853FF4ED646FED62A6B" blockId="5.[151,1437,638,1817]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">
<emphasis id="7D8F9C38FFCE4853FF4ED646FEBC2BDA" bold="true" box="[151,274,638,664]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Postpedicel yellow; fore coxa yellow or all coxae brown; wing brown infuscated, anal lobe narrower basally; tergite 1 velvety brown pruinose, tergites 2–5 shiny brown with inconspicuous setae; surstyli subsymmetrical, both thickened medially, with inner margins straight; apex of phallic guide stout and long, with two thin setae ventrally; ejaculatory apodeme funnel-shaped, leaning to one side; phallus trifid, with ejaculatory ducts short and backwards directed.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4F44402AFFCE4853FF1ED70AFE4E2CBB" blockId="5.[151,1437,638,1817]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">
<emphasis id="7D8F9C38FFCE4853FF1ED70AFE462A0E" bold="true" box="[199,488,818,844]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">Intraspecific variability.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="2B6A3DDBFFCE4853FE36D70BFD252A0F" author="Rafael, J. A." box="[495,651,819,845]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" pagination="353 - 390" refId="ref19665" refString="Rafael, J. A. (1990) Revisao das especies neotropicais do genero Cephalops Fallen (Diptera: Pipunculidae). Acta Amazonica, 20, 353 - 390." type="journal article" year="1990">Rafael (1990)</bibRefCitation>
provided a complete description and illustrations of the Brazilian 
<typeStatus id="9040FE88FFCE4853FAAED70BFF4F2A33" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">holotype</typeStatus>
; however, we found variations in the Colombian specimens. Because of this, we provide a comparison of the variations between the Colombian and Brazilian specimens (between parenthesis, when comparable). MALE. Length 
<quantity id="8803EDCFFFCE4853FF37D7A7FEEB2AFB" box="[238,325,927,953]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.1" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" unit="mm" value="3.1">3.1 mm</quantity>
(
<emphasis id="7D8F9C38FFCE4853FE8CD7A7FE332AFA" box="[341,413,927,952]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">versus</emphasis>
<quantity id="8803EDCFFFCE4853FE7DD7A7FE552AFB" box="[420,507,927,953]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.6" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" unit="mm" value="4.6">4.6 mm</quantity>
in the 
<typeStatus id="9040FE88FFCE4853FD90D7A7FD1E2AF8" box="[585,688,927,954]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">holotype</typeStatus>
); postcranium gray pruinose laterally and brown pruinose dorsally (
<figureCitation id="D7C05CAFFFCE4853FF79D7FBFEB02A9F" box="[160,286,963,989]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–29" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1780,1804]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1756]" captionTargetId="figure-30@6.[151,1436,181,1756]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 17–29. Cephalops amapaensis Rafael, 1990. (IAvH–M945). Male. 17, Habitus, left lateral view; 18, Habitus, dorsal view; 19, Antenna; 20, Thorax, dorsal view; 21, Wing; 22, Abdomen, dorsal view; 23, Tergites and sternites 6 and 7, ventral view; 24, Terminalia, dorsal view; 25, Left surstylus, lateral view; 26, Right surstylus, lateral view; 27, Hypandrium and gonopods, ventral view, 28, Phallic guide and phallus, left lateral view; 29, Ejaculatory apodeme." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592655" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592655/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">Fig. 17–18</figureCitation>
); scape brown (
<figureCitation id="D7C05CAFFFCE4853FE09D7FBFD8A2A9F" box="[464,548,963,989]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–29" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1780,1804]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1756]" captionTargetId="figure-30@6.[151,1436,181,1756]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 17–29. Cephalops amapaensis Rafael, 1990. (IAvH–M945). Male. 17, Habitus, left lateral view; 18, Habitus, dorsal view; 19, Antenna; 20, Thorax, dorsal view; 21, Wing; 22, Abdomen, dorsal view; 23, Tergites and sternites 6 and 7, ventral view; 24, Terminalia, dorsal view; 25, Left surstylus, lateral view; 26, Right surstylus, lateral view; 27, Hypandrium and gonopods, ventral view, 28, Phallic guide and phallus, left lateral view; 29, Ejaculatory apodeme." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592655" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592655/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
); frontal triangle with inconspicuous brown callus (
<emphasis id="7D8F9C38FFCE4853FBB5D7FBFB1A2A9E" box="[1132,1204,963,988]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">versus</emphasis>
frontal triangle with narrowed black callus); scutellum with few tiny setae (
<figureCitation id="D7C05CAFFFCE4853FCCBD7DFFCC72D43" box="[786,873,999,1025]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–29" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1780,1804]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1756]" captionTargetId="figure-30@6.[151,1436,181,1756]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 17–29. Cephalops amapaensis Rafael, 1990. (IAvH–M945). Male. 17, Habitus, left lateral view; 18, Habitus, dorsal view; 19, Antenna; 20, Thorax, dorsal view; 21, Wing; 22, Abdomen, dorsal view; 23, Tergites and sternites 6 and 7, ventral view; 24, Terminalia, dorsal view; 25, Left surstylus, lateral view; 26, Right surstylus, lateral view; 27, Hypandrium and gonopods, ventral view, 28, Phallic guide and phallus, left lateral view; 29, Ejaculatory apodeme." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592655" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592655/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">Fig. 20</figureCitation>
); membrane brown infuscate (
<figureCitation id="D7C05CAFFFCE4853FB1ED7DFFAB32D43" box="[1223,1309,999,1025]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–29" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1780,1804]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1756]" captionTargetId="figure-30@6.[151,1436,181,1756]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 17–29. Cephalops amapaensis Rafael, 1990. (IAvH–M945). Male. 17, Habitus, left lateral view; 18, Habitus, dorsal view; 19, Antenna; 20, Thorax, dorsal view; 21, Wing; 22, Abdomen, dorsal view; 23, Tergites and sternites 6 and 7, ventral view; 24, Terminalia, dorsal view; 25, Left surstylus, lateral view; 26, Right surstylus, lateral view; 27, Hypandrium and gonopods, ventral view, 28, Phallic guide and phallus, left lateral view; 29, Ejaculatory apodeme." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592655" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592655/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
); all coxae brown (
<figureCitation id="D7C05CAFFFCE4853FF36D033FEEC2D67" box="[239,322,1035,1061]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–29" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1780,1804]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1756]" captionTargetId="figure-30@6.[151,1436,181,1756]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 17–29. Cephalops amapaensis Rafael, 1990. (IAvH–M945). Male. 17, Habitus, left lateral view; 18, Habitus, dorsal view; 19, Antenna; 20, Thorax, dorsal view; 21, Wing; 22, Abdomen, dorsal view; 23, Tergites and sternites 6 and 7, ventral view; 24, Terminalia, dorsal view; 25, Left surstylus, lateral view; 26, Right surstylus, lateral view; 27, Hypandrium and gonopods, ventral view, 28, Phallic guide and phallus, left lateral view; 29, Ejaculatory apodeme." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592655" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592655/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
) (
<emphasis id="7D8F9C38FFCE4853FE82D033FE0D2D66" box="[347,419,1035,1060]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">versus</emphasis>
fore coxae yellow to light brown); femora light yellow in proximal third, yellow in distal three thirds (
<figureCitation id="D7C05CAFFFCE4853FEF3D017FED32D0B" box="[298,381,1071,1097]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–29" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1780,1804]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1756]" captionTargetId="figure-30@6.[151,1436,181,1756]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 17–29. Cephalops amapaensis Rafael, 1990. (IAvH–M945). Male. 17, Habitus, left lateral view; 18, Habitus, dorsal view; 19, Antenna; 20, Thorax, dorsal view; 21, Wing; 22, Abdomen, dorsal view; 23, Tergites and sternites 6 and 7, ventral view; 24, Terminalia, dorsal view; 25, Left surstylus, lateral view; 26, Right surstylus, lateral view; 27, Hypandrium and gonopods, ventral view, 28, Phallic guide and phallus, left lateral view; 29, Ejaculatory apodeme." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592655" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592655/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
) (
<emphasis id="7D8F9C38FFCE4853FE41D017FE4E2D0A" box="[408,480,1071,1096]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">versus</emphasis>
femora entirely yellow); hind tibia with posterior erect setae medially (
<emphasis id="7D8F9C38FFCE4853FAC3D017FACC2D0A" box="[1306,1378,1071,1096]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">versus</emphasis>
hind tibia without posterior erect setae medially); abdomen brown, tergite 1 velvety brown pruinose, with six brown and long setae laterally, tergites 2–5 shiny brown with inconspicuous setae (
<figureCitation id="D7C05CAFFFCE4853FC26D04FFB2D2DD3" box="[1023,1155,1143,1169]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–29" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1780,1804]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1756]" captionTargetId="figure-30@6.[151,1436,181,1756]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 17–29. Cephalops amapaensis Rafael, 1990. (IAvH–M945). Male. 17, Habitus, left lateral view; 18, Habitus, dorsal view; 19, Antenna; 20, Thorax, dorsal view; 21, Wing; 22, Abdomen, dorsal view; 23, Tergites and sternites 6 and 7, ventral view; 24, Terminalia, dorsal view; 25, Left surstylus, lateral view; 26, Right surstylus, lateral view; 27, Hypandrium and gonopods, ventral view, 28, Phallic guide and phallus, left lateral view; 29, Ejaculatory apodeme." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592655" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592655/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">Figs 18, 22</figureCitation>
) (
<emphasis id="7D8F9C38FFCE4853FB44D04FFB4B2DD2" box="[1181,1253,1143,1168]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">versus</emphasis>
tergite 1 brown pruinose basally, gray pruinose distally interrupted medially, tergites 2–3 with shiny black spot posterolaterally, tergites 4–5 brown pruinose on 1/4–1/5 basally, other apical areas black), tergites and sternites 6 and 7 as in 
<figureCitation id="D7C05CAFFFCE4853FA9FD087FA392D9B" box="[1350,1431,1215,1241]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–29" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1780,1804]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1756]" captionTargetId="figure-30@6.[151,1436,181,1756]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 17–29. Cephalops amapaensis Rafael, 1990. (IAvH–M945). Male. 17, Habitus, left lateral view; 18, Habitus, dorsal view; 19, Antenna; 20, Thorax, dorsal view; 21, Wing; 22, Abdomen, dorsal view; 23, Tergites and sternites 6 and 7, ventral view; 24, Terminalia, dorsal view; 25, Left surstylus, lateral view; 26, Right surstylus, lateral view; 27, Hypandrium and gonopods, ventral view, 28, Phallic guide and phallus, left lateral view; 29, Ejaculatory apodeme." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592655" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592655/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">Fig. 23</figureCitation>
; surstyli subsymmetrical, slightly equal to epandrium length, completely setose, both surstyli thickened medially, thin at bases and apices, with inner margins straight (
<figureCitation id="D7C05CAFFFCE4853FD2FD13FFCE52C63" box="[758,843,1287,1313]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–29" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1780,1804]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1756]" captionTargetId="figure-30@6.[151,1436,181,1756]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 17–29. Cephalops amapaensis Rafael, 1990. (IAvH–M945). Male. 17, Habitus, left lateral view; 18, Habitus, dorsal view; 19, Antenna; 20, Thorax, dorsal view; 21, Wing; 22, Abdomen, dorsal view; 23, Tergites and sternites 6 and 7, ventral view; 24, Terminalia, dorsal view; 25, Left surstylus, lateral view; 26, Right surstylus, lateral view; 27, Hypandrium and gonopods, ventral view, 28, Phallic guide and phallus, left lateral view; 29, Ejaculatory apodeme." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592655" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592655/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">Fig. 24</figureCitation>
); both surstyli with tips forward-directed when seen in lateral view (
<figureCitation id="D7C05CAFFFCE4853FE90D113FE632C07" box="[329,461,1322,1349]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–29" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1780,1804]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1756]" captionTargetId="figure-30@6.[151,1436,181,1756]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 17–29. Cephalops amapaensis Rafael, 1990. (IAvH–M945). Male. 17, Habitus, left lateral view; 18, Habitus, dorsal view; 19, Antenna; 20, Thorax, dorsal view; 21, Wing; 22, Abdomen, dorsal view; 23, Tergites and sternites 6 and 7, ventral view; 24, Terminalia, dorsal view; 25, Left surstylus, lateral view; 26, Right surstylus, lateral view; 27, Hypandrium and gonopods, ventral view, 28, Phallic guide and phallus, left lateral view; 29, Ejaculatory apodeme." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592655" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592655/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">Figs 25–26</figureCitation>
); gonopods subsymmetrical, left gonopod slightly thinner than right (
<figureCitation id="D7C05CAFFFCE4853FB07D113FA9D2C07" box="[1246,1331,1323,1349]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–29" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1780,1804]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1756]" captionTargetId="figure-30@6.[151,1436,181,1756]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 17–29. Cephalops amapaensis Rafael, 1990. (IAvH–M945). Male. 17, Habitus, left lateral view; 18, Habitus, dorsal view; 19, Antenna; 20, Thorax, dorsal view; 21, Wing; 22, Abdomen, dorsal view; 23, Tergites and sternites 6 and 7, ventral view; 24, Terminalia, dorsal view; 25, Left surstylus, lateral view; 26, Right surstylus, lateral view; 27, Hypandrium and gonopods, ventral view, 28, Phallic guide and phallus, left lateral view; 29, Ejaculatory apodeme." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592655" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592655/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">Fig. 27</figureCitation>
); apex of phallic guide stout and long, with two thin setae ventrally (
<figureCitation id="D7C05CAFFFCE4853FCE5D177FC3C2C2B" box="[828,914,1359,1385]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–29" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1780,1804]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1756]" captionTargetId="figure-30@6.[151,1436,181,1756]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 17–29. Cephalops amapaensis Rafael, 1990. (IAvH–M945). Male. 17, Habitus, left lateral view; 18, Habitus, dorsal view; 19, Antenna; 20, Thorax, dorsal view; 21, Wing; 22, Abdomen, dorsal view; 23, Tergites and sternites 6 and 7, ventral view; 24, Terminalia, dorsal view; 25, Left surstylus, lateral view; 26, Right surstylus, lateral view; 27, Hypandrium and gonopods, ventral view, 28, Phallic guide and phallus, left lateral view; 29, Ejaculatory apodeme." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592655" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592655/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">Fig. 28</figureCitation>
); ejaculatory apodeme funnel-shaped, leaning to one side (
<figureCitation id="D7C05CAFFFCE4853FEF8D14BFED82CCF" box="[289,374,1395,1421]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–29" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1780,1804]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1756]" captionTargetId="figure-30@6.[151,1436,181,1756]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 17–29. Cephalops amapaensis Rafael, 1990. (IAvH–M945). Male. 17, Habitus, left lateral view; 18, Habitus, dorsal view; 19, Antenna; 20, Thorax, dorsal view; 21, Wing; 22, Abdomen, dorsal view; 23, Tergites and sternites 6 and 7, ventral view; 24, Terminalia, dorsal view; 25, Left surstylus, lateral view; 26, Right surstylus, lateral view; 27, Hypandrium and gonopods, ventral view, 28, Phallic guide and phallus, left lateral view; 29, Ejaculatory apodeme." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592655" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592655/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
); phallus trifid, with ejaculatory ducts short and backwards directed (
<figureCitation id="D7C05CAFFFCE4853FB5BD14BFB792CCF" box="[1154,1239,1395,1421]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–29" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1780,1804]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1756]" captionTargetId="figure-30@6.[151,1436,181,1756]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 17–29. Cephalops amapaensis Rafael, 1990. (IAvH–M945). Male. 17, Habitus, left lateral view; 18, Habitus, dorsal view; 19, Antenna; 20, Thorax, dorsal view; 21, Wing; 22, Abdomen, dorsal view; 23, Tergites and sternites 6 and 7, ventral view; 24, Terminalia, dorsal view; 25, Left surstylus, lateral view; 26, Right surstylus, lateral view; 27, Hypandrium and gonopods, ventral view, 28, Phallic guide and phallus, left lateral view; 29, Ejaculatory apodeme." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592655" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592655/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">Fig. 28</figureCitation>
). FEMALE (
<figureCitation id="D7C05CAFFFCE4853FAB2D14BFF4F2CF3" captionStart="FIGURES 30–32" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1132,1156]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1108]" captionTargetId="figure-19@7.[151,1436,181,1108]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 30–32. Cephalops amapaensis Rafael, 1990. (LEUA–M954). Female. 30, Habitus, left lateral view; 31, Abdomen, right lateral view; 32, Ovipositor, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592658" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592658/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">Figs 30–32</figureCitation>
). Tergites 2–5 predominantly gray pruinose laterally (
<emphasis id="7D8F9C38FFCE4853FCE5D1AFFC2A2CF2" box="[828,900,1431,1456]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">versus</emphasis>
tergite 4–5 brown pruinose basally, shiny black posterolaterally); ovipositor base light brown, brownish-pruinose (
<figureCitation id="D7C05CAFFFCE4853FC5AD183FC792C97" box="[899,983,1467,1493]" captionStart="FIGURES 30–32" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1132,1156]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1108]" captionTargetId="figure-19@7.[151,1436,181,1108]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 30–32. Cephalops amapaensis Rafael, 1990. (LEUA–M954). Female. 30, Habitus, left lateral view; 31, Abdomen, right lateral view; 32, Ovipositor, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592658" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592658/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">Fig. 31</figureCitation>
); piercer yellow, except the base brown, apex shiny, straight (
<figureCitation id="D7C05CAFFFCE4853FEA6D1E7FE7A2CBB" box="[383,468,1503,1529]" captionStart="FIGURES 30–32" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1132,1156]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1108]" captionTargetId="figure-19@7.[151,1436,181,1108]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 30–32. Cephalops amapaensis Rafael, 1990. (LEUA–M954). Female. 30, Habitus, left lateral view; 31, Abdomen, right lateral view; 32, Ovipositor, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592658" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592658/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">Fig. 32</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
